Reviewed outside endoscopy and pathology reports and radiology reports and lab data.  His ALT is mildly elevated at 49, and fatty liver disease is described on his CT-scan.  There are no focal hepatic nodules noted.
#1 Sigmoid colon cancer, question descending colon cancer
Mr. Kling is referred for further treatment of sigmoid colon cancer.  His pathology slides also describe cancer in a specimen from the descending colon, where two polyps measuring 2-mm and 4-mm were removed.  I suspect this may be contaminant; however, at this time we will proceed with a repeat colonoscopy to re-visualize the area.  The primary lesion in the sigmoid colon has been tattooed.  His outside CT will be sent to radiology for interpretation.  Laboratory studies including a CBC, chemistry panel, and also a lipid screen and PSA will be checked.  Given his history of hypertension and that he is not currently on medical therapy, we will check an six-hour ambulatory blood pressure monitor and request hypertension evaluation is this is significantly abnormal.  I will also request an overnight oximetry for assessment of possible sleep apnea as this will affect his perioperative monitoring.  I will follow-up with the patient at the conclusion of his tests with colorectal surgery consultation.  Discussed the plan of care in detail with the patient and answered questions.
#2 Preoperative medical evaluation
Chest x-ray, ECG, six-hour ambulatory blood pressure monitor, and overnight oximetry are pending.  Once these are obtained and satisfactory, the patient is OK for anesthesia.
Discussed with Dr. Bobby Edwards; note to follow.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: Yes, on file at HHFI.

